The paper deals with cross-lingual text classification, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a new ensemble learning method, which falls under the category of machine learning and could be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning) as well. The paper also involves feature representation and classification, which are common topics in information retrieval (IR) and artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.IR and cs.AI likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper uses publicly available multilingual text collections, which could involve computer vision (CV) techniques for data preprocessing, making cs.CV a possible sub-category as well.
